                    "body": "Can you please provide code for each operation?\r\n\r\nNote we have made no guarantees of identical bytes at the protocol level as long as the semantic content of the message is the same. This permits implementations to make their own decisions regarding padding / memory allocation. The integration tests validate that the messages are semantically compatible (they are interpreted as being the \"same data\")",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=wesm",
                        "name": "wesm",
                        "key": "wesmckinn",
                        "avatarUrls": {
                            "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?ownerId=wesmckinn&avatarId=29931",
                            "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&ownerId=wesmckinn&avatarId=29931",
                            "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&ownerId=wesmckinn&avatarId=29931",
